# Repo-root .dockerignore — applies to both backend/ and ui/ Dockerfiles.
#
# The build context for both is the repository root (the workspace
# lockfile + offchain/ tree are needed for pnpm workspace resolution
# and the SDK build), so this is the .dockerignore BuildKit honours.
# The per-package backend/.dockerignore + ui/.dockerignore exist only
# as documentation for contributors editing those images; Docker does
# not read them when the build context is the repo root.

# Workspace + IDE
.git
.github
.idea
.vscode
.DS_Store
**/node_modules
**/.cache
**/.turbo

# Build outputs (re-built inside the image)
backend/dist
offchain/dist
ui/dist

# Bulk dev-only directories
docs
papers
bench
crypto/ref/target

# Test outputs
ui/playwright-report
ui/test-results
**/coverage

# Local secrets / dotenvs — must never be baked into an image
.env
.env.*
**/.env
**/.env.*
!.env.example
!**/.env.example

# Logs
*.log

# Note: artifacts/ is intentionally NOT excluded. backend/Dockerfile
# bakes artifacts/${NETWORK}/addresses.json into the image as the
# bootstrap-derived protocol address book. Per-network artifact dirs
# are < 250KB so the cost is trivial.
